      <title>Healing / Curing Ward AAs reset OOC regen counter; other issues</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11726#M11726</link>
      <description>I brought this up in serverwide cleric last night, and thought a post here might receive some attention (as opposed to the one I made in the Veteran's Lounge).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Currently, healing and curing wards (the AA ones) are resetting the out-of-combat regeneration counter.&amp;nbsp; So, if one of those wards is active in the area, you'll never be able to enter OOC regen.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I may be wrong, but it also appeared that Ward of Absolution (at rank 1) only seems to be firing off every 24 seconds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I think these healing / curing wards were underpowered to begin with, and I can't see using the healing ward at all any more if it's going to block the far superior OOC regen from happening.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If this is working 'as intended' then we need a way to easily get rid of the ward once it's been cast; a /pet go away would be nice, if it actually worked on the wards. As it is, I use my goblin dedicant staff to summon the goblin familiar and then I dismiss him by clicking off the buff; that also kills all of my other wards and pets (including jesters).&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
