    <item>
      <title>Representing the Gods</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11641#M11641</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;We are representations of our gods and the gods are something that are so ingrained into the game, yet we receive little in the terms of different religious based quests. Other than mostly newbie quests from home town guilds, as we grow away the faith is just represented through some spells and other such. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;From a quest stand point the classic deity symbols were and are still race/class defining item for well atleast Innoruuk worshipping Frogloks, Humans and Dark elves. Expanding on these obviously would be logical, albeit it time consuming to balance. However, new coding offers some interesting choices such as Aura's or Familiars. So I think for a symbol series 2.0 to manifest itself would be overdue to help flesh out priests of differing religions a little bit without overbalancing one over the other.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Another way is graphically. I see alot of potential with the models currently and with the future player models. In terms of current, the most obvious are avatar forms. We're the only priest class that doesn't receive some sort of altered form. An illusion of this sort has two functions, first fun and lore aspects respectively but also the potential for an additional buff to statistics that has no stacking issues with our current line up. It's an interesting avenue really and so many ways to go about it. Such as the Chaos and Order theme for clerics, or having "evil" clerics and "good" clerics having different avatar form. Or each deity or group of deities bestowing upon their worshippers a different model for their avatar form. Thus differentiating between the different religions. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The second way, dealing with the potential of new models is gaining the aspects of the gods. Such as evil clerics opening up blood red hair and horns with a demonic tail, or good clerics having golden or silvery hair and a halo. While this doesn't do anything directly statistical, it does however play onto further developing customizibility for long term clerics in the service of thier gods. From a lore stand point you become an embodiment of your god and overtime you grow to become a divine creature. This could be even done for other priests, such as human druids of Tunare gaining more elf-like features and what not.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What are your thoughts?&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Vjik on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;09-26-2006&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;01:13 PM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
