      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;I have a new question if this could be considered. Essentially, people&#xD;
have been saying casting buffs / elixirs has been producing 0 aggro at&#xD;
all and they have been keeping out of battle state and have been power&#xD;
medding under the OoC status as a result. Yet when they do burst heals,&#xD;
they definately are procurring aggro alot more often. (this is what others have been stating).&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Buff aggro has been parsed at ~10 points of hate that is subject to SCS&#xD;
and aggro mods. Heal aggro has yet to be properly defined but is always&#xD;
greater than buff aggro when noticed.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
It is known, especially with Rashere confirming, that mobs have an&#xD;
intelligence factor that determines the chance whether a cast&#xD;
beneficial spell gets noticed or not, that is, whether hate is produced&#xD;
or not effectively putting someone on aggro. Therefore my question is:&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
"Is the chance an npc notices a cast beneficial spell identical for all&#xD;
spell types, or, are npc's less likely to notice a spell the less aggro&#xD;
it is? That is, will buff aggro be noticed less than direct heals or is&#xD;
it all the same chance?"&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Something to that effect Niph :) I thought it would be appropriate what&#xD;
with OoC changes and "in battle/out of battle" statuses to learn more&#xD;
on whether certain heals (elixirs/promised) are more likely to keep&#xD;
someone in "power med" mode than other healing methods.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
