    <item>
      <title>Better late than never</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11620#M11620</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Some answers to the weekly questions:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Healing someone will get you on the aggro list of a creature that hates your target, however it will not in all cases change your faction if said creature dies. For instance, healing in Kael Drakkal typically gives no faction for killing giants unless the healer performs something more offensive like nukes or melee attacks.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Is this intended and if so can you describe the mechanics of faction hits in the case of heals?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;(Rashere) When you heal someone, the NPC only has a chance to put you on their hatelist.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;That chance is based on the intelligence of the NPC.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;The times you don’t get faction are due to not ending up on the hatelist.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Currently, Touch of the Divine doesn't strip detrimental effects like it was initially intented. Is it something you still want to implement and what can you tell us about ETA, difficulty etc?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;(Oshran) &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;There are currently no plans to have TotD remove negative effects for 3 reasons.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;1) Clerics already have a number of tools for removing detrimental effects after TotD triggers. 2) A few raids rely on the fact that the only way to remove certain detrimental effects is to perform a certain raid-specific action or die…&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;3) From a lore standpoint, TotD should either strip all positive AND negative effects (if you are being resurrected) or should strip no effects (if you are being saved from death).&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;The spell relies on the latter interpretation.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Additionally, even though there is no real evidence, people complain that it doesn't work well with Delay Death maxed. Can you confirm that the check is when you die, not when you go below 0 HP?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;(Oshran continued) &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The check is made when you die, not when you reach 0 hit points.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;This is intended because players can cross the 0 hp mark several times in a very short period of time (i.e. multiple checks), but they can only die once.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I'd like also to feedback that TotD5 triggers rate has been parsed at approximately 8% (I was expecting 10 or 15%).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;(Oshran continued) &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;ToTD5 should have a chance to trigger 10% of the time.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;This has been confirmed by our testing department.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;If it's triggering less then 10%, please /bug report it with detailed steps to reproduce.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0033ff&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Tue, 26 Sep 2006 23:38:31 GMT</pubDate>
