      <title>Faction</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11585#M11585</link>
      <description>I was with a group doing Bellfast 5 this evening, and at the end of it, one of the group members commented that I would probably have raised my faction enough to be able to get the Bellfast series of missionsmyself. I went and spoke to the NPC, and he ignored me as usual. A bit of investigation showed that although I had been a participant in every fight during the mission, because I had mostly only healed, I had recieved no faction modifier for most of the kills.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I know I have come accross this before when trying to raise Dranik Loyallist faction, and I had to try to tag every mob to make sure my faction was raised, but it seems unfair to me that clerics should be penalised on factions for doing exactly what our main purpose is in a group i.e., healing. I get plently of random faction messages allying me with meaningless groups while doing the same thing throughout EQ, so why should these two (and probably others that I am unaware of) be different and require me to directly interact with the mob?&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
