    <item>
      <title>Some info about our AAs</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11576#M11576</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I got this from Kyth today:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ward of Purity is the cleric AA that cures 1, 2 or 3 (depending on rank) poison and disease counters. Is it intended that it cures every other tick (every 12s) instead of every tick?&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;(Oshran) Intended.&amp;nbsp; Wards work by repeatedly casting instant duration spells with specific recast timers.&amp;nbsp; Ward of Purity's recast timer was tuned around ten seconds.&amp;nbsp; All wards that I've looked into have a recast timer of at least ten seconds.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV align=left&gt;It seems the cleric undead DoT AA (Turn Undead / Wrack Undead / Eradicate Undead) does not stack when several clerics cast it on the same creature. Is this intented?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV align=left&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV align=left&gt;Reference thread at &lt;A href="http://www.eqclerics.org/forums/showthread.php?t=20994&amp;amp;page=6" target=_blank&gt;&lt;FONT color=#000000&gt;eqclerics.org&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/A&gt;.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;(Oshran) Intended.&amp;nbsp; Buff and bebuff lines generally fill the same buff slot which prevents them from stacking.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;About the last answer, my understanding was that DoTs are allowed to stack on a mob if from different casters. This was a change put in place to help DoT classes (ex: necro) in raids. I must have been mistaken, can a raiding necro comment?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
