    <item>
      <title>Raising the Complete Heal base, CH is obsolete.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11556#M11556</link>
      <description>Complete Heal has not completely healed since the Planes of Power era&#xD;
when tanks started reaching 10k and more hit points.&amp;nbsp; Currently tanks&#xD;
hit 17k+ (at an Anguish level, we aren't going to discuss with PoR&#xD;
gear) so Complete heal is only 50% healing.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Fall damage was upped so that it was effective, as well as other things including Ranger heals but complete heal was left alone.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;font color="#cc66ff"&gt;&lt;b&gt;I feel we need a complete heal base raise, an aa that will allow us to do so, or an Improved Complete Heal spell.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Even with modifiers CH only heals for 9600 and takes 10 seconds to&#xD;
cast, it's original base heal is 7k.&amp;nbsp; Ancient Hallowed Light only takes 2.8 seconds to cast and heals&#xD;
for 6056 hp.&amp;nbsp; Meaning that CH is obsolete.&amp;nbsp; If the based was raised to&#xD;
actually do it's job and COMPLETE heal it would be used more in groups&#xD;
and in raid situations.&amp;nbsp; As it is now AHL is more efficient then CH&#xD;
(granting that you have the mana pool that typically comes with&#xD;
achieving ancient spells).&amp;nbsp; In raid situations when you don't have AHL&#xD;
Pious Light is used.&amp;nbsp; Now fast heal rotations will always be needed&#xD;
under certain circumstances but I fully believe that if Complete Heal&#xD;
was Improved it would be used more in both raid and group situations.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
Even people that do not have AHL use other heals rather then CH, not&#xD;
just because of the cast time but because it just simply isn't&#xD;
efficient in doing it's intended job.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
It wouldn't make it to powerful either since it would actually then do&#xD;
what it was intended to do... completely heal.&amp;nbsp; It will still cost 400&#xD;
mana, take 10 seconds to cast, and will be uneffected by most&#xD;
modifiers, including spell haste, as it is currently but it will then&#xD;
do it's actual job of COMPLETELY healing.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
What is everyone elses view on this?&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Froakah Sternenstaub&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
70/850 Cleric&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
Clan nan Dreolan&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
