      <title>Consolidating the question of the week</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11519#M11519</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Here is what I asked, verbatim, not counting repeated questions. If you would like to have a question answered please make a separate post so we can debate it, or send me a PM.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;......&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Ward of Purity is the cleric AA that cures 1, 2 or 3 (depending on rank) poison and disease counters. Is it intended that it cures every other tick (every 12s) instead of every tick?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;......&lt;/P&gt;As monsters become more and more powerful, they deal more and more damage during the 10 seconds of&amp;nbsp;a CH. Soon Complete Healing will not heal enough to keep a tank alive in standard group encounters.&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Do you plan to introduce upgrades&amp;nbsp;to CH or otherwise maintain a line of long casting time heal spells, or will you let CH as it is and focus only on upgrades to the Light and Remedy lines?&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;......&lt;/P&gt;"Where do the Developers see clerics heading in terms of raiding (new encounter mechanics, etc) and grouping styles (in terms of variety for that elusive "Secondary Role" that we do not currently have), and how would they go about achieving it?"&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;......&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Abundant Healing 3 was supposed to be reduced from a 10% to 9% trigger rate this patch. Did the change make it?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The problem was how&amp;nbsp;Abundant Healing&amp;nbsp;and Gift of Mana interact with each other. GoM is considered a better AA and with this change AH3 would not lower the trigger rate of GoM5.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Rashere said it was AH5 that was supposed to be changed and that yes it did get changed.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;......&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Here is what Rashere posted about Touch of the Divine the cleric AA:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
TotD now only checks when you actually die. It's not modified by anything. It's a flat percent check based on your rank in the ability. The actual percent will not be stated (sorry folks!), but the chance increases with each rank. It's basically a "get out of death" free card although it doesn't go off often enough that you can rely on it, which is by design.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;When TotD triggers, it puts a DA style buff on the player, so they drop to the bottom of hate lists just like DA. In addition, it heals the player over the next 6 ticks. Previously, because of the bug that was causing it to also work like Divine Aura and trigger at low health, it would strip the buffs of players. That no longer happens.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;In addition, with this patch, the amount of healing it does has been increased and made it remove all detrimental effects on the cleric when the ability triggers. This effect doesn't vary by rank. The only thing that changes as you increase ranks is that you have a greater chance to be saved when you die.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Currently, TotD doesn't strip detrimental effects. Is it something you still want to implement and what you tell us about ETA, difficulty etc?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Additionally, even though there is no real evidence, people complain that it doesn't work well with Delay Death maxed. Can you confirm that the check is when you die, not when you go below 0 HP?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;......&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Is there any plan to eventually have the cleric self buff line (ex: Armor of the Pious) stack with the shaman focus line (ex: Talisman of Wunshi) ?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
